    "blackboard": "┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│         PRESENT CONTINUOUS PASSIVE VOICE                  │\n├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                           │\n│  FORM: am/is/are + being + V3(过去分词)                   │\n│                                                           │\n│  主动：[Doer] + am/is/are + V-ing + [Receiver]            │\n│  被动：[Receiver] + am/is/are + being + V3 (+ by Doer)    │\n│                                                           │\n│  WHEN TO USE:                                             │\n│  ① 不知道谁在做                                           │\n│  ② 强调承受者                                             │\n│  ③ 执行者显而易见                                         │\n│                                                           │\n│  ⚠ being 不可省略！                                       │\n│  ⚠ 不及物动词无被动 (happen, occur, exist...)             │\n│                                                           │\n│  例：Antelopes ARE BEING PROTECTED.                       │\n│      Forests ARE BEING DESTROYED.                         │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘",
    "exercises": "【基础作业】（全体必做）\nI. 将下列主动句改为被动句：\n1. Scientists are studying the endangered species.\n2. The government is building a new wildlife reserve.\n3. Illegal hunters are killing elephants for ivory.\n4. Volunteers are planting trees in the habitat.\n5. People are polluting the river with plastic waste.\n\nII. 用所给动词的现在进行时被动形式填空：\n6. The Tibetan antelope ______ (protect) in the Changtang Nature Reserve.\n7. Their wool ______ (sell) in the black market illegally.\n8. New laws ______ (make) to punish illegal hunting.\n9. The population ______ (monitor) by scientists every day.\n10. Many forests ______ (destroy) to make room for farms.\n\n【提高作业】（A班必做，B班选做）\nIII. 写3个句子，描述中国正在进行的野生动物保护行动，使用现在进行时被动语态。\n\n【参考答案——教师用】\nI. 1. The endangered species IS BEING STUDIED (by scientists).\n   2. A new wildlife reserve IS BEING BUILT (by the government).\n   3. Elephants ARE BEING KILLED for ivory (by illegal hunters).\n   4. Trees ARE BEING PLANTED in the habitat (by volunteers).\n   5. The river IS BEING POLLUTED with plastic waste (by people).\nII. 6. is being protected  7. is being sold  8. are being made\n    9. is being monitored  10. are being destroyed\nIII. 评分标准：①语法正确（am/is/are+being+V3）②内容相关③词汇使用。示例：Giant pandas are being protected in Sichuan. New reserves are being built across China. Illegal hunting is being stopped by strict laws.",
