        "content": "【PPT 02 范文展示——网络安全博客】\n\n【教师台词】\"Today we write a blog post about online safety. A blog post is different from an essay — it's like talking to a friend. Let's read a model blog post.\"\n\n▲ PPT展示范文：\n\nTITLE: I Almost Lost My Account. Here's What I Learned.\n\nHOOK: Last month, I almost lost my social media account. Someone tried to hack it. I was lucky — but I learned a big lesson.\n\nPERSONAL EXPERIENCE: It happened on a Tuesday. I got a message: \"Click here to verify your account.\" The link looked real. I almost clicked it. But something felt wrong. I checked the sender's address — it was misspelled! I reported it and changed my password immediately.\n\nADVICE: Here's what I've learned: First, never click links from strangers. Second, use strong passwords — mix letters, numbers, and symbols. Third, check the sender's address carefully. Fourth, turn on two-factor authentication. These simple steps can protect your account.\n\nCONCLUSION: The internet has changed our lives, but it has also created new dangers. Stay smart, stay safe!\n\n【教师台词】\"With your partner, identify the 5 parts.\"\n\n【PPT 03 博客结构图解——五部分流程图】\n\n【预设回答】\n- \"Title: 'I Almost Lost My Account.' It's personal and creates curiosity.\" (教师：\"Good — it makes you want to read.\"）\n- \"Hook: 'Last month, I almost lost...' — grabs attention with a scary story.\" (教师：\"Right — start with drama.\"）\n- \"Personal experience: specific details — Tuesday, the message, the misspelling.\" (教师：\"Details make it real and believable.\"）\n- \"Advice: 4 specific tips with imperatives.\" (教师：\"Notice: 'never click,' 'use strong passwords,' 'check the address' — all specific actions.\"）\n- \"Conclusion: a reminder. Notice the present perfect passive: 'has changed... has also created.'\" (教师：\"Yes! Grammar from last lesson!\"）\n\n【板书时机】教师在黑板中央画出五部分流程图：\n  Title → Hook → Experience → Advice → Conclusion\n\n【PPT 04 语气对比——正式vs.博客vs.随意】\n\n【教师台词】\"A blog post has a SPECIAL tone — not too formal, not too casual. Compare:\"\n\n| 太正式(✗) | 博客语气(✓) | 太随意(✗) |\n|----------|-----------|----------|\n| It is recommended that users employ complex passwords. | Use strong passwords — mix letters, numbers, and symbols. | lol just use a hard password tbh |\n\n【教师台词】\"The MIDDLE one is right for a blog. It uses imperative sentences ('Use strong passwords'), dashes for emphasis, and specific details. It sounds like a smart friend giving advice.\""
